From 226ce98df88a925a0307d79347849f4718f3effe Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shaohui Xie <Shaohui.Xie@nxp.com>
Date: Mon, 11 Apr 2016 14:23:33 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1289/1429] dts: fsl-ls2080a-rdb: disable EMDIO1

EMDIO1 has Cortina PHYs connected, since Cortina PHY acting as
fixed-link, and being treated as fixed-link in driver, we disable the
EMDIO1 to avoid probing Cortina PHY which has non-standard MMD address
will cause error dump.

Signed-off-by: Shaohui Xie <Shaohui.Xie@nxp.com>
[Original patch taken from QorIQ-SDK-V2.0-20160527-yocto]
Signed-off-by: Yanjiang Jin <yanjiang.jin@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2080a-rdb.dts |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2080a-rdb.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2080a-rdb.dts
index e7dcfb6..155d7fc 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2080a-rdb.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2080a-rdb.dts
@@ -133,6 +133,7 @@
 };
 
 &emdio1 {
+	status = "disabled";
 	/* CS4340 PHYs */
 	mdio1_phy1: emdio1_phy@1 {
 		reg = <0x10>;
